'''Maxim Rasimovich Sharafutdinov''' ({{lang-ru|<U+041C><U+0430><U+043A><U+0441><U+0438><U+0301><U+043C> <U+0420><U+0430><U+0441><U+0438><U+043C><U+043E><U+0432><U+0438><U+0447> <U+0428><U+0430><U+0440><U+0430><U+0444><U+0443><U+0442><U+0434><U+0438><U+0301><U+043D><U+043E><U+0432>}}; born September 15, 1980) is a [[Russia]]n [[journalist]], [[television presenter]] of [[Channel One (Russia)|Channel One]].

== Biography ==
Maxim Sharafutdinov was born on September 15, 1980, in [[Kazan]], [[Tatar ASSR]], [[USSR]]. Played in [[KVN]]. Graduated from Kazan State Technical University. Worked in the TV of [[Tatarstan]].

On March 25, 2010, Sharafutdinov presented the inauguration of the president of Tatarstan.

